This memorandum, addressed to the Secretary of State, delegates the authority to direct the drawdown of defense articles and services, as well as military education and training, to provide assistance to Ukraine. The delegated authority is in accordance with section 506(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. The aggregate value of the drawdown is up to $450 million. The memorandum is signed by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and directs the Secretary of State to publish it in the Federal Register.